definition.value: A nitroso compound that is N-undecylnitrous hydrazide carrying double bonds at positions 1,2,4, and 7. It is a long-chain fatty acyl CoA synthetase inhibitor and interferes with lipid metabolism by inhibiting the de novo synthesis of glycerolipids and cholesterol esters.
A flavonoid oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the hydroxy group at position 7 of myricetin 3-O-beta-D-glucopyranoside. The major species at pH 7.3.

A flavonoid oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 7 of the flavonoid ring of myricetin 3-O-[(6-O-trans-4-coumaroyl-beta-D-glucosyl)-(1->2)-alpha-L-rhamnoside]. Identified in Fig. S21 peak 2 of PMID:29967287.
Identified in Fig. S21 peak 3

A flavonoid oxoanion resulting from the deprotonation of the hydroxy group at positio 7 of the flavonoid moiety of myricetin 3-O-[(6-O-acetyl-beta-D-glucosyl)-(1->2)-alpha-L-rhamnoside]. Identified in PMID: 23549747 Fig. S21 peak 4.
An EC 3.1.1.* (carboxylic ester hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of retinoid isomerohydrolase (EC 3.1.1.64).
A tripeptide composed of one L-glutamine and two L-cysteine units joined by peptide linkages.
A tripeptide composed of L-lysine, L-glutamic acid and L-threonine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tripeptide composed of glycine, L-alanine and L-alanine residues joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tripeptide composed of one L-lysine and two L-glutamic acid units joined by peptide linkages.

A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is guanosine 3',5'-cyclic monophosphate(1-) in which the hydrogen at position 8 on the purine fragment has been replaced by a nitro group; major species at pH 7.3.
Major species at pH 7.3
methylimidazole crosslink between an L-cysteine residue and an L-arginine residue (PMID:30323285: Fig 4g and extended data Fig 8).
An acetophenone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 4, and by a sulfooxy group at position 5. It is a metabolite of the Chinese medicine 'Shuangdan' granule.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3'-phosphate(3-) in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as oleoyl.
A tripeptide composed of glycine, L-arginine and L-proline joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tripeptide composed of L-lysine, L-serine and L-tryptophan joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tripeptide formed from L-serine, L-leucine and L-serine residues joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
An 8-oxocitronellyl enol in which the chiral centre has S configuration.

A cyclopentapyran that is (4aR,7aS)-1,4a,5,6,7,7a-hexahydrocyclopenta[c]pyran substituted at position 1 by an oxo group and at positions 4 and 7 by methyl groups, respectively (the 4aR,7S,7aS-diastereomer). An iridoid monoterpenoid isolated from several Nepeta plant species.

An N-glycoprotein resulting from the formal condensation of the side-chain carboxamide group of the L-asparagine residue at positions 417 and 448 of the genome polyprotein of hepatitus C virus subtype 1a (positions 35 and 66 in PMID:18187336, respectively) with the hemiacetal group of D-mannosylated alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc. The position of one of the mannosyl groups is not known; in the structure shown, one of the R atoms represents a D-mannopyranosyl group; all remaining R atoms = H.
Major species at pH 7.3
A cyclopentapyran that is (4aR,7aS)-1,4a,5,6,7,7a-hexahydrocyclopenta[c]pyran substituted at position 1 by a hydroxy group and at positions 4 and 7 by methyl groups (the 4aR,7S,7aS)-diastereomer.

An amino heptasaccharide that is MAN-3 glycan, alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc, in which either (a) two hydroxy groups in one of the terminal mannosyl groups have each undergone glycosylation with a molecule of D-mannopyranose, or (b) one of the hydroxy groups has undergone dimannosylation. The position of the additional mannosyl groups is not known. In the structure shown, either two of the R atoms each represent a D-mannopyranosyl group, or one of the R atoms represents a di-D-mannosyl group; all remaining R atoms = H.
An 8-oxocitronellyl enol in which the chiral centre has R configuration.

An N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl group obtained formally by removal of the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of di-(D-mannosylated) alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc. In the structure shown, either two of the R atoms each represent a D-mannopyranosyl group, or one of the R atoms reprsents a di-D-mannosyl group; all remaining R atoms = H.

An N-glycoprotein resulting from the formal condensation of the side-chain carboxamide group of the L-asparagine residues in the genome polyprotein of hepatitus C virus subtype 1a with the hemiacetal group of D-mannosylated alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc. It has been found at positions 417, 423, 448, 540, 556, and 623 of the protein (positions 35, 41, 66, 158, 174, and 241 in PMID:18187336, respectively). In the structure shown, either two of the R atoms each represent a D-mannopyranosyl group, or one of the R atoms reprsents a di-D-mannosyl group; all remaining R atoms = H.
A 2-hydroxy-6-oxo-2,4-heptadienoate which has 2Z,4E configuration. Obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of (2Z,4E)-2-hydroxy-6-oxohepta-2,4-dienoic acid, it is the major species at pH 7.3.
